{"title_page": "Barry Lines", "text_new": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|         name = Barry Lines\n|     fullname =\n|       height =\n|   birth_date = {{birth date|1942|5|16|df=y}}\n|  birth_place = [[Bletchley]], England\n|   death_date =\n|  death_place =\n| currentclub  =\n|     position = [[Forward (association football)#Outside forward|Outside Left]]\n|       years1 = \u20131960\n|       years2 = 1960\u20131970\n|       clubs1 = [[Bletchley Town F.C.|Bletchley Town]]\n|       clubs2 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n|        caps1 =\n|        caps2 =  266\n|       goals1 = \n|       goals2 =  48\n}}\n'''Barry Lines''' (born 16 May 1942) was an [[English people|English]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who played 266 league matches for [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]. He played either as an [[Forward (association football)#Outside forward|Outside]] or [[Forward (association football)#Inside forward|Inside forward]] on the left-hand side.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.11v11.com/players/barry-lines-34180/5 Barry Lines - 11v11]\n*[http://hugmansfootballers.com/player/11755 Barry Lines - Hugmans Footballers]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lines, Barry}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football outside forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|         name = Barry Lines\n|     fullname =\n|       height =\n|   birth_date = {{birth date|1942|5|16|df=y}}\n|  birth_place = [[Bletchley]], England\n|   death_date =\n|  death_place =\n| currentclub  =\n|     position = [[Forward (association football)#Outside forward|Outside Left]]\n|       years1 = \u20131960\n|       years2 = 1960\u20131970\n|       clubs1 = [[Bletchley Town F.C.|Bletchley Town]]\n|       clubs2 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n|        caps1 =\n|        caps2 =  266\n|       goals1 = \n|       goals2 =  48\n}}\n'''Barry Lines''' (born 16 May 1942) was a [[English people|English]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who played 266 league matches for [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]. He played either as an [[Forward (association football)#Outside forward|Outside]] or [[Forward (association football)#Inside forward|Inside forward]] on the left-hand side.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.11v11.com/players/barry-lines-34180/5 Barry Lines - 11v11]\n*[http://hugmansfootballers.com/player/11755 Barry Lines - Hugmans Footballers]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lines, Barry}}\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football outside forwards]]\n", "name_user": "Orenburg1", "label": "safe", "comment": "sp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Lines"}
{"title_page": "Low-flying aircraft", "text_new": "'''Low-flying aircraft''' may mean:\n*Aircraft used in [[Low flying military training]].\n*Aircraft flying near an airport, either when taking off or landing.\n*Aircraft flying below the allowed minimum height for the type within an [[aviation authority]]'s jurisdiction, such as\n:*[[Hang-gliders]]\n:*[[Microlights]]\n:*[[Drone (aircraft)]]\n:*[[Balloon (aeronautics)]]\n:*[[Kites]] {{cn|date=May 2016|reason=No known definition of a low-altitude kite}}\n:*[[Search and rescue]] aircraft.\n\n==In the arts==\n*''[[Low-Flying Aircraft and Other Stories]]'', a book by J. G Ballard\n*''[[Aparelho Voador a Baixa Altitude]]'' (literally, \"flying machines at low altitude\"), a Portuguese film\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ceiling (aircraft)]]\n*{{section link|Altitude|Altitude in aviation}}\n\n{{dab}}\n", "text_old": "'''Low-flying aircraft''' may mean:\n*Aircraft used in [[Low flying military training]].\n*Aircraft flying near an airport, either when taking off or landing.\n*Aircraft flying below the allowed minimum height for the type within an [[aviation authority]]'s jurisdiction, such as\n:*[[Hang-gliders]]\n:*[[Microlights]]\n:*[[Drone (aircraft)]]\n:*[[Balloon (aeronautics)]]\n:*[[Kites]] {{cn|date=May 2016|reason=No known definition of a low-altitude kite}}\n:*[[Search and rescue]] aircraft.\n\n==In the arts==\n*''[[Low-Flying Aircraft and Other Stories]]'', a book by J. G Ballard\n*''[[Aparelho Voador a Baixa Altitude]]'' (literally, \"flying machines at low altitude\"), a Portuguese film\n\n==See also==\n*[[ceiling (aircraft)]]\n*{{section link|Altitude|Altitude in aviation}}\n\n{{dab}}\n", "name_user": "Cryptopocalypse", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:Capitalization", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Low-flying_aircraft"}
{"title_page": "List of Community episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Community'' episodes}}\n[[File:Community 2009 logo.svg|right|300px]]\n''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]'' is an American [[comedy]] television series which premiered on September 17, 2009, on [[NBC]]. The series follows a group of students at a community college in the fictional locale of Greendale, Colorado. The series heavily uses [[meta-humor]] and pop culture references, often parodying film and television clich\u00e9s and tropes. After five seasons on NBC, ''Community'' moved to [[Yahoo! Screen]] for its sixth and final season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/06/community-returning-yahoo-season-6/|title=\u2018Community\u2019 Revived To Air On Yahoo In Fall With 13 Episodes |publisher=Deadline|first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=June 30, 2014 |accessdate=June 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color1     = #304a84\n| link1      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2009\u201310)\n| episodes1  = 25\n| start1     = {{Start date|2009|9|17}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2010|5|20}}\n| network1   = [[NBC]]\n\n| color2     = #ffd66a\n| link2      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2010\u201311)\n| episodes2  = 24\n| start2     = {{Start date|2010|9|23}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2011|5|12}}\n\n| color3     = #51408b\n| link3      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2011\u201312)\n| episodes3  = 22\n| start3     = {{Start date|2011|9|22}}\n| end3       = {{End date|2012|5|17}}\n\n| color4     = #dde557\n| link4      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2013)\n| episodes4  = 13\n| start4     = {{Start date|2013|2|7}}\n| end4       = {{End date|2013|5|9}}\n\n| color5     = #bcad8e\n| link5      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2014)\n| episodes5  = 13\n| start5     = {{Start date|2014|1|2}}\n| end5       = {{End date|2014|4|17}}\n\n| color6     = #3bbeda\n| link6      = <includeonly>List of Community episodes</includeonly>#Season 6 (2015)\n| episodes6  = 13\n| start6     = {{Start date|2015|3|17}}\n| end6       = {{End date|2015|6|2}}\n| network6   = [[Yahoo! Screen]]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n\n===Season 1 (2009\u201310)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 1)}}\n{{:Community (season 1)}}\n\n===Season 2 (2010\u201311)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 2)}}\n{{:Community (season 2)}}\n\n===Season 3 (2011\u201312)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 3)}}\n{{:Community (season 3)}}\n\n===Season 4 (2013)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 4)}}\n{{:Community (season 4)}}\n\n===Season 5 (2014)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 5)}}\n{{:Community (season 5)}}\n\n===Season 6 (2015)===\n{{Main article|Community (season 6)}}\n{{:Community (season 6)}}\n\n==Webisodes==\n===''The 5 As'' (2009)===\n''The 5 As of Greendale'' is a webisode series that appeared before ''Community''{{'}}s pilot was broadcast. The first six videos are set up as informational videos about enrolling at the fictitious Greendale Community College. The last two serve as in-character outtakes of Dean Isakson (portrayed by the series' creator, [[Dan Harmon]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/community/video/categories/the-5-as-webisodes/1148284/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110162714/http://www.nbc.com/community/video/categories/the-5-as-webisodes/1148284/|archivedate=January 10, 2011|title=Webisodes : The 5 As Webisodes|work=NBC.com|accessdate=October 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=The 5 As |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Greendale's First Straight A: Accessibility\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Greendale's Second Straight A: Affordability\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = More Straight A's: Air Conditioning / Awesome New Friends\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = Greendale's Final Straight A: A Lot of Classes\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = Pat Isakson Screws Up - Part 1\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = Pat Isakson Screws Up - Part 2\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''The Community College Chronicles'' (2009)===\n''The Community College Chronicles'' are two webisodes that act as Abed Nadir's student films. The webisodes parody events that happen on the main show ''Community''. In the episode \"Debate 109\", the webisodes were seen by the characters making them believe Abed can see the future. The webisodes also appear on the Greendale Community College's website part of the A/V department's page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greendalecommunitycollege.com/av_dept/|title=The A/V Department|work=Greendale Community College|accessdate=October 27, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091219060920/http://www.greendalecommunitycollege.com/av_dept/|archivedate=December 19, 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=The Community College Chronicles |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = My Hobo Days\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|