rk=NBC.com|accessdate=October 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=The 5 As |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Greendale's First Straight A: Accessibility\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Greendale's Second Straight A: Affordability\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = More Straight A's: Air Conditioning / Awesome New Friends\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = Greendale's Final Straight A: A Lot of Classes\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = Pat Isakson Screws Up - Part 1\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = Pat Isakson Screws Up - Part 2\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|8|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''The Community College Chronicles'' (2009)===\n''The Community College Chronicles'' are two webisodes that act as Abed Nadir's student films. The webisodes parody events that happen on the main show ''Community''. In the episode \"Debate 109\", the webisodes were seen by the characters making them believe Abed can see the future. The webisodes also appear on the Greendale Community College's website part of the A/V department's page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greendalecommunitycollege.com/av_dept/|title=The A/V Department|work=Greendale Community College|accessdate=October 27, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091219060920/http://www.greendalecommunitycollege.com/av_dept/|archivedate=December 19, 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=The Community College Chronicles |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = My Hobo Days\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|11}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Pop Quiz\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|11}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Spanish Videos'' (2010)===\n''Spanish Videos'' are two webisodes (plus a trailer) featuring Star-Burns ([[Dino Stamatopoulos]]), Abed ([[Danny Pudi]]), and Se\u00f1or Chang ([[Ken Jeong]]). Chang assigns the class a video assignment and Abed and Star-Burns make a space epic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2010/04/22/community-webisode-premiere-exclusive/|title='Community' webisode premiere: Watch the two-part EXCLUSIVE here!|work=Entertainment Weekly|first=Sandra|last=Gonzalez|date=April 22, 2010|accessdate=December 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=Spanish Videos |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Part 1\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|22|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Part 2\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|22|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Study Break'' (2010)===\n''Study Break'' is a series of three mini-episodes of ''Community'' exclusive to [[Comcast]]'s [[Comcast#Xfinity rebranding|Xfinity]] TV and to the season one DVD of ''Community''. The mini-episodes focus on 90 second study breaks during a Spanish study session.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/44666/community-the-complete-first-season/|title=Community: The Complete First Season|work=DVD Talk|first=Jason|last=Bailey|date=September 14, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=Study Break |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Stop using your brain\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|3|5}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Truth or Dare\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|3|5}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Generation Gap\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|3|5}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Road to the Emmys'' (2010)===\n''Road to the Emmys'' are three webisodes about the study group on their way to an Emmy party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.givememyremote.com/remote/2010/08/30/communitys-road-to-the-emmys/|title=COMMUNITY\u2019s Road to the Emmys|work=Give Me My Remote |first=Marisa|last=Roffman|date=August 10, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=Road to the Emmys |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Playing Britta Off\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|8|29}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Seat Fillers\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|8|29}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Playing Jeff Off\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|8|29}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Dean Pelton's Office Hours'' (2010)===\n''Dean Pelton's Office Hours'' are three webisodes focusing on Dean Pelton ([[Jim Rash]]) solving student problems.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/11/04/dean-peltons-office-hours_n_779003.html|title=Dean Pelton's 'Office Hours': 'Community' Favorite Gets His Own Web Series! (VIDEO)|work=[[Huffington Post]] |first=Katla|last=McGlynn|date=November 4, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=The Community College Chronicles |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pamphlet Serious\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|11|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Hair Piece\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|11|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Independent Study Assistant\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|11|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Abed's Master Key'' (2012)===\n''Abed's Master Key'' are three animated webisodes in which Abed becomes Dean Pelton's assistant and is given a master key to Greendale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/03/03/community-animated-shorts/|title='Community' cast starring in three new animated shorts|work=Entertainment Weekly|first=Darren|last=Franich|date=March 3, 2012|accessdate=March 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |anchor=Abed's Master Key |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Part One\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|3|7}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Part Two\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|3|7}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Part Three\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|3|7}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n}}\n\n=== Others === \n{{Episode table |anchor=Other webisodes |background=#224c8c |overall= |title=40 |airdate=15 |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Community Season 4 Premieres... Someday\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|10|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = A short trailer for the fourth season of ''Community'' where Troy ([[Donald Glover]]) and Abed (Danny Pudi) present their fake morning talk show, ''Troy & Abed in the Morning'', to wish everyone a \"Happy October 19th\" and to explain why the fourth-season premiere has been delayed.<ref>{{cite news|last=Snierson|first=Dan|title='Community': 'Troy & Abed in the Morning' addresses the show's delay -- VIDEO|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/10/19/community-delay-season-4-troy-abed/|accessdate=April 4, 2014|newspaper=Entertainment Weekly|date=October 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Harris|first=Aisha|title=Happy Oct. 19, From the Cast of Community|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2012/10/19/community_october_19th_video_gives_fans_hope_for_season_4_s_eventual_arrival.html|accessdate=April 4, 2014|newspaper=Slate|date=October 19, 2012}}</ref> \n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Miracle on Jeff's Street\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|12|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = An animated special of the ''Community'' gang reuniting just in time to save Jeff\u2019s Christmas.<ref>{{cite news|last=Fitzpatrick|first=Kevin|title=\u2018Community\u2019 Season 5 Draws Up Animated Holiday Prequel \"Miracle on Jeff\u2019s Street\"|url=http://screencrush.com/community-season-5-christmas-animated-miracle-on-jeffs-street/|accessdate=April 4, 2014|newspaper=Screen Crush|date=December 19, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = 224c8c\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Abed and the Dean Share a Moment in a Honda\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|3|31}}\n |ShortSummary    = 